Dr. Michael Galli appears by phone, is sworn by the Court and is examined by Attny Siehr.  Cross exam by Attny White.  Redirect.  No other witnesses called.  Arguments by both attorneys.  Court does not believe there are many complex issues to this case and if it goes to trial would allow some leading questions if defendant testifies.  Court believes the defendant can proceed.  Attny Siehr indicates that based on the Courts decision, defendant will enter a plea today but needs to fill out plea questionnaire.  At 11:13 a.m. parties return.  No contest plea entered by defendant.  Court advises party of their rights, finds factual basis, accepts defendant's waiver of their rights, the plea made, and finds guilty.  Arguments as to penalty.  Court imposes a fine & costs totaling $894.00.  Appeal rights.

Attny Siehr spoke with defendant's mother and forgot to tell defendant about today's hearing.  $500 cash warrant authorized, Court will not sign until 1/25.  At 12:10 p.m. defendant appears with counsel and his mother.  Court quashes warrant and resets the hearing.
